{"word":"Sarah","slug":"sarah","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Sarah</b> <a href=\"#/H8283\">H8283</a> <br/> 1. Called also Sarai:<br/> - Wife of Abraham<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=11&verse=31'>Gen 11:31</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=12&verse=5'>Gen 12:5</a> <br/> - Near of kin to Abraham<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=12&verse=20'>Gen 12:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=20&verse=12'>Gen 20:12</a> <br/> - Abraham represents her as his sister, and Abimelech, king of Gerar, takes her; she is restored to Abraham by means of a dream<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=20&verse=14'>Gen 20:14</a> <br/> - Is sterile; gives her maid, Hagar, to Abraham as a wife<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=16&verse=3'>Gen 16:3</a> <br/> - Her jealousy of Hagar<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=16&verse=6'>Gen 16:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=21&verse=14'>Gen 21:14</a> <br/> - Her miraculous conception of Isaac<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=17&verse=21'>Gen 17:21</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=18&verse=15'>Gen 18:15</a> <br/> - Name changed from Sarai to Sarah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=17&verse=15'>Gen 17:15</a> <br/> - Gives birth to Isaac<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=21&verse=3'>Gen 21:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=21&verse=8'>Gen 21:8</a> <br/> - Death and burial of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=23'>Gen 23</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=25&verse=10'>Gen 25:10</a> <br/> - Character of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=58&chapter=11&verse=11'>Heb 11:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=60&chapter=3&verse=6'>1Pe 3:6</a> <br/> 2. See <a href='S:Serah'>Serah</a><br/> <a href='S:Serah'>Serah</a>"}]}